<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900928-0120</DOCNO><DOCID>900928-0120.</DOCID><HL>   Technology:   Merck to Change Drug's Name</HL><DATE>09/28/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B6</SO><CO>   MRK G.HFA</CO><IN>DRUG MANUFACTURERS (DRG)</IN><LP>   WEST POINT, Pa. -- Merck Sharp andamp; Dohme, the pharmaceuticalarm of Merck andamp; Co., said it is changing the trade name ofLosec, the medication used for peptic disorders, to Prilosec.   The company said the change was being made to preventfurther confusion between the drug and a medication made byHoechst AG's Hoechst-Roussel unit called Lasix, used to treathigh blood pressure. It said it received necessary federalapprovals.</LP><TEXT>   Merck said it received reports that some patients who hadbeen prescribed Losec were &quot;erroneously&quot; given Lasix, whichis also used to prevent bleeding in horses. Merck is based inRahway, N.J.</TEXT></DOC>